To create, join, or see faction info, visit the faction registrar.

Fedit commands:

-Syntax: fedit <field> <value>
-fedit
Display current faction information.

-fedit save
-fedit name <string>
-fedit shortname <string>
-fedit keywords <string>
-fedit password <string>
-fedit numranks <number>
-fedit ranks <rank#> <title>
-fedit affiliation <faction>

-fedit permissions <rank#> <permission string (see below)>
Permissions list:
r = recruit
p = promote
t = treasurer
e = edit
l = lock
a = ambassador
s = scribe

-fedit colors <color1> <color2> <color3>

-fedit flags <flag>
Flag list:
active      - sets faction to active, immortal only
locked      - locks faction, immortal only
recruitment - sets faction as currently recruiting
hidden      - hides faction from non-members
members     - hides membership from non-members
ranks       - hides rank infomation from non-members

-fedit relations <target faction> [ war | peace | none ]

-fedit patron <patron>
See "help pantheon" for a list of deities.




